Chilean Stocks: Concha y Toro, La Polar, Sudamericana de Vapores

-- B y   L e o n   L a z a r o f f   a n d   J a m e s   A t t w o o d
-- 
2011-04-08T19:28:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-08/chilean-stocks-endesa-enersis-parque-arauco-vina-concha.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 3:09 p.m. New York time.  The Ipsa index fell 0.6 percent to 4,712.97.  Cia Sudamericana de Vapores SA (VAPORES)   declined 4.6
percent, the most in three weeks, to 366.5 pesos. Shareholders
of Latin America’s largest container shipper approved a proposal
to sell as much as $1 billion in new shares to shore up the
company’s finances in a meeting today in Valparaiso,  Chile .  Empresas La Polar SA (LAPOLAR)   slid 1.9 percent to
2,739.6 pesos. The Luksic family, Chile’s richest according to
Forbes, isn’t looking to buy a stake in the department-store
operator, Guillermo Luksic told reporters in Valparaiso, Chile.  Vina Concha y Toro SA (CONCHA)   rose the most in a month,
climbing 2.9 percent to 1,182.4 pesos. Chile’s largest wine
exporter reported an 18 percent increase in first-quarter sales.
Preliminary sales rose to 77.7 billion pesos from 66.1 billion a
year earlier, it said in an e-mailed statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
